<br>
Race:  Seen lots of good arguments for just about each race but Nano, so it more or less comes down to preference.  Atrox is good for hitpoints and Brawls but nano casting will suffer.  Solitus is good all around, catch-all race.  Personally, I like my Opifex.  I have good damage with fists, awesome Brawls with implants, and can cast all the nanos I could want.  Hit points are somewhat lower but I haven't suffered because of that.<br>
<br>
Other tips:  Max main abilities like Brawl, MA, Close Combat Evade.  Get Parry up, not necessarily maxing each level but keep it up.  Get your Nano skills up so you can use the important programs like Sub. Guidance, Dirty Fighter, etc.  First-Aid and Heal nanos skills are good to have as high as you can, especially if you have lower health and plan to do PvP.<br>
<br>
Don't know what else to say but get Implants.  Implants really make the MA class and will significantly add to your damage output.  Since you won't be constantly upgrading weapons and don't have a ton of Nano Programs to buy, you'll be able to save up enough pretty easily to put a good set together.<br>
<br>
